Detailed Description

The class PbRecord will be used to store phone book entries in non-volatile memory. All methods to take access to the saved Pb entry data are defined in this class. Because some phone numbers could be added to one Pb entry the class PbNumberRecord was generated

void PbRecord::MarkDeleted (   )  [virtual]
 

Method sets the current provider data state to "deleted". This means that the saved data are invalid and could not be read anymore. This method is called if phone book entries will be deleted. Furtermore during the parent class initialisation if the provider data file will be created new with empty phone book entries.

Reimplemented from Record.
